#. <section class="sutta" id="sn46.5"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn46.5:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 46"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 46"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.5:0.2"
msgid "1. Pabbatavagga"
msgstr "1. Mountains"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn46.5:0.3"
msgid "5. Bhikkhusutta"
msgstr "5. A Monk"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.5:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn46.5:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn46.5:1.3"
msgid "“‘bojjhaṅgā, bojjhaṅgā’ti, bhante, vuccanti."
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of the ‘awakening factors’."

msgctxt "sn46.5:1.4"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, ‘bojjhaṅgā’ti vuccantī”ti?"
msgstr "How are the awakening factors defined?”"

msgctxt "sn46.5:1.5"
msgid "“Bodhāya saṃvattantīti kho, bhikkhu, tasmā ‘bojjhaṅgā’ti vuccanti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicant, they’re called awakening factors because they lead to awakening."

msgctxt "sn46.5:1.6"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhu, satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ "
"nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ … pe … upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti "
"vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant develops the awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of "
"principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity, which "
"rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go."

msgctxt "sn46.5:1.7"
msgid ""
"Tassime satta bojjhaṅge bhāvayato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi "
"cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"As they develop the seven awakening factors, their mind is freed from the "
"defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance."

msgctxt "sn46.5:1.8"
msgid "Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "sn46.5:1.9"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’"

msgctxt "sn46.5:1.10"
msgid "Bodhāya saṃvattantīti, bhikkhu, tasmā ‘bojjhaṅgā’ti vuccantī”ti."
msgstr "They’re called awakening factors because they lead to awakening.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.5:1.11"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
